name: 2wice Vol9 Nº1
description: Cunningham & Rauschenberg The pioneering work of two titans of dance and art is vividly portrayed in this special issue. Robert Rauschenberg's groundbreaking costume design for Merce Cunningham's dance company is represented through their decades-long collaboration. The issue is designed as a panorama that weaves their signature dances into a dramatic retrospective. Working with photographer Joachim Ladefoged, the company performs for the camera under the direction of Merce Cunningham. Printed on translucent, fabric-like paper in vivid colors, the issue captures Cunningham's radical choreography and Rauschenberg s equally avant-garde costumes, both of which remain landmarks in the history of art. The issue's design is presented in french-folded pages, allowing the choreography to move in and out from the spine in a continuous line. Quite the beautiful volume. Performers: Merce Cunningham Dance Company Visual Artists: Joachim Ladefoged, Robert Rauschenberg Design: Pentagram Writer: Nancy Dalva [2wice arts foundation, new york city /2006 / ~150 perfect-bound, french-folded pages with die-cuts / full color with metallic inks / OUT OF PRINT] For more images/info: http://2wice.org/cunningham/

name: 2wice Vol9 Nº2
description: How to Pass, Kick, Fall and Run 2wice's "How to" issue surveys the do-it-yourself ethic through essays on paint-by-number kits, books by avant-garde artists, step-by-step choreographic sequences, and ready-made architecture. The title is taken from a Merce Cunningham dance that served as point of reference for the issue. Performers: Tom Gold, Mark Morris Dance Company, Merce Cunningham Dance Company Visual Artists: Josef Astor, Nina Katchadourian, Jens Umbach, Katherine Wolkoff Design: Pentagram Writer: Ian Berry, Nancy Dalva, Irene Gammel, Sarah Goldstein, Robert Kronenburg, Micki McGee, David Platzker, William Smith [2wice arts foundation, new york city /2006 / ~150 perfect-bound pages / full color] For more images/info: http://www.2wice.org/howtopass/
